  "name": "Consciousness of the Atom",
  "description": "Alice Bailey's 1922 lecture series tracing consciousness from the atom to the solar system. Seven lectures build a single argument: that every form in nature — from the smallest atom to the greatest star — is a living, conscious entity at some stage of evolutionary unfoldment. This grammar extracts the factual propositions about reality (not just the seven rays) and presents them as contemplation cards.\n\nSource: Alice A. Bailey, *The Consciousness of the Atom*, Lucifer Publishing Co., 1922. Public domain (pre-1929 US publication).\n\nPUBLIC DOMAIN ILLUSTRATION REFERENCES: Sacred geometry and atomic/cosmic diagrams from early 20th century theosophical publications. Annie Besant and C.W. Leadbeater's *Occult Chemistry* (1908) contains relevant atomic clairvoyant diagrams. Ernst Haeckel's *Art Forms in Nature* (1904) provides beautiful biological form illustrations that echo the atom-to-organism consciousness thread.",
  "grammar_type": "custom",
  "creator_name": "PlayfulProcess",
